<subSubSection id="CBC06566FFB8FF9964BAFE97FB9BFE1C" pageId="8" pageNumber="225" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="836536EDFFB8FF9964BAFE97FB9BFE1C" blockId="8.[151,1126,328,447]" pageId="8" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB8FF9964BAFE97FEDDFEFC" bold="true" box="[151,268,328,351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="225">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="44DA4D6EFFB8FF9965A9FE97FE2CFEFC" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1896" box="[388,509,328,351]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Pseudethas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB8FF9965A9FE97FE2CFEFC" box="[388,509,328,351]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="225">Pseudethas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by parallel-sided elytra with flattened surface; elytral base considerably wider than pronotal base; tempora often convex, sometimes parallel; pronotum usually with mid-longitudinal impression which may sometimes be only very slightly developed; middle and posterior male tibiae with apical tooth on inner side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
